---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="elio Docs"
  description="Find elio configuration paths, theme locations, and links to the full reference."
>
  <section class="page-intro">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">DOCS</p>
      <h1>Configure and theme elio</h1>
      <p>
        Find the right config paths for your platform, start from the bundled themes, and jump into
        the main repository when you need the full reference.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="docs-block docs-grid">
        <article class="doc-card">
          <h2>Config paths</h2>
          <p>Linux and BSD use <code>~/.config/elio/</code> or <code>$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/elio/</code>.</p>
          <p>macOS uses <code>~/Library/Application Support/elio/</code>.</p>
          <p>Windows uses <code>%APPDATA%\elio\</code>.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="doc-card">
          <h2>Theme paths</h2>
          <p>The theme file is named <code>theme.toml</code> in the same platform config directory.</p>
          <p>Bundled examples live in <code>examples/themes/</code> in the main repository.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="doc-card">
          <h2>Install and reference</h2>
          <p>Install commands live on the install page. The full reference lives in the main repository.</p>
          <p>
            <a href="/install">Open install page</a>
          </p>
          <p>
            <a href="https://github.com/elio-fm/elio#readme" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Read the README</a>
          </p>
          <p>
            <a href="https://github.com/elio-fm/elio/tree/main/examples/themes" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
              Browse bundled themes
            </a>
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
